    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-21T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-21T13:00:00-05:00" n="310"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/170</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-21T18:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.51 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8336. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1"
                        >Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 50. At the request of Foreign Office, I agreed to the following proposal for
                        <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> which was made to Swedish
                    representatives. …<note n="1" xml:id="d310fn1">Terms similar to those in
                        telegram No. 8242, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1201">p.
                            1201</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>If this proposal accepted do you intend have one-half chartered for the United
                    States and one-half to British excepting <hi rend="italic">Jemtland</hi> and <hi
                        rend="italic">Österland?</hi> It occurs to me if you do, the British may ask
                    that one-half the Dutch boats secured on <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> be
                    chartered to them and therefore it would be advisable to arrange. You should
                    charter all Dutch boats in American ports and have the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Jemtland</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Österland</hi> return to you for a
                    round trip and let the English arrange with French and Italians for the 100,000
                    tons Swedish ships which are to go in danger zone. Please give instructions
                    quickly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
